.TH REGEDIT 1 "2026-06-01" "libreg 0.1.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
regedit \- web-based offline registry editor
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B regedit
.RB [ \-\-port
.IR N ]
.RB [ \-\-bind
.IR ADDR ]
.RB [ \-\-hive
.IR FILE
.RB [ \-\-root
.IR LABEL ]]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B regedit
serves a browser based registry editor for offline hive files, modeled on the
Windows registry editor. It offers the same browsing and editing (keys, values
of every REG type, import and export of
.B .reg
files) plus features the core library exposes that the Windows editor does
not: editable SDDL security descriptors, hive structural validation, an on-disk
structure inspector (base block fields and a cell map), and a two-hive diff.
.PP
Hives come from the mount map (see
.BR reg (1)),
or a single
.B \-\-hive
.I FILE
can be served under
.B \-\-root
.I LABEL
(default HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE). Each request opens the hive file, performs its
operation, and saves on edit, so changes persist immediately.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BI \-\-port " N"
TCP port to listen on (default 7890).
.TP
.BI \-\-bind " ADDR"
Address to bind (default 127.0.0.1).
.TP
.BI \-\-hive " FILE"
Serve a single hive file instead of the mount map.
.TP
.BI \-\-root " LABEL"
Root label for the
.B \-\-hive
file.
.SH SECURITY
.B regedit
performs no authentication and edits hive files directly. Bind it to a loopback
or trusted interface only. The packaged systemd unit binds 127.0.0.1 by default.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR reg (1),
.BR sc (1)
